  <h2 id="common-mistakes">Common Counter Mistakes and How to Fix Them</h2>

  <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1rem; margin: 1.5rem 0;">
    <div style="background: #fef2f2; border: 1px solid #fca5a5; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 8px;">
      <strong style="color: #dc2626;">❌ Common Mistakes</strong>
      <ul style="margin: 0.5rem 0 0; padding-left: 1.2rem; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        <li>Using 個 for people (should be 人)</li>
        <li>Using 匹 for large animals (should be 頭)</li>
        <li>Forgetting sound changes (さんほん → さんぼん)</li>
        <li>Confusing 時 (o'clock) with 時間 (duration)</li>
        <li>Using 枚 for books (should be 冊)</li>
        <li>Saying にひき instead of にひき (2 is regular, 3 changes)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div style="background: #f0fdf4; border: 1px solid #86efac; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 8px;">
      <strong style="color: #16a34a;">✅ Tips</strong>
      <ul style="margin: 0.5rem 0 0; padding-left: 1.2rem; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        <li>When in doubt, use つ for objects</li>
        <li>People always use 人 (never つ)</li>
        <li>Think about the object's shape to choose the counter</li>
        <li>Practice sound changes for 1, 3, 6, 8, 10 specifically</li>
        <li>Flat = 枚, long = 本, bound = 冊</li>
        <li>Listen for counters in dramas and anime</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="practice-tips">How to Practice and Remember Counters</h2>
  <p>Counters are best learned through real-world practice, not memorization lists. Here are effective methods:</p>

